Posted: Sun Apr 07, 2013 9:21 pm
Pocky Is God wrote:Does anyone fly sparge? http://www.northernbrewer.com/shop/delu ... allon.htmlI'm thinking I can do so with this kit, but unsure. Anyone care to help me out here?I've been fly sparging since the mid 1980's. You don't need $250 worth of kit to do it The upper tank holds the sparge water - mine is a white plastic bucket with a hole drilled in the side at the bottom and a piece of tube JAMMED in it (the hole is about 1/8th inch smaller than the outside diameter of the tube). I wrap this bucket with an old fleece shirt and some towels for insulation. I found a couple of tiny C clamps that look like this at my hardware store:I eye-ball the flow rate - you'll get it pretty quickly. You measure the time to can fill a quart jar and make adjustments. The only rule of thumb I have to pass on is that you want to keep a pool of sparge water covering your grain bed until the end. Put a T on the end of the tube that inlets into the top of your mash tun and thats it. I have well under $20 into it - its lasted me about 15 years so far.
