Posted: Wed Apr 10, 2013 1:19 pm
GohanIYIan wrote:Pocky Is God wrote:Does anyone fly sparge? http://www.northernbrewer.com/shop/delu ... allon.htmlI'm thinking I can do so with this kit, but unsure. Anyone care to help me out here?I batch sparge with essentially that exact set-up. Efficiency is typically in the 75-80% range so I've never felt any need to increase the complexity by recirculating the wort.There are people in this world that recirculate until the wort runs clear (sparkling clear) - this is overdoing it. You want to reduce the amount of grain husks and trub getting into the brew kettle. If you recirc about 3 pint glasses you will get ~85% of it - including a few large chunks. On the other hand if this step seems unrelaxed and worried to you take GohanIYIan's advice and just skip it. You'll probably never know - it makes more of a difference in a commercial size kettle. This is one of those things that the big guys do that homebrewers just copy. They do it to reduce the size of the pile of gunk in the bottom of the brew kettle and reduce the amount of Irish moss they have to add (in addition to reducing the amount of tannins dissolved in the beer).
Pocky Is God
