why split it into 2x5gallon? just do a 10 gallon boil. hot water in one, mash the other, sparge into the pot and boil away.buy 20 gallons of water. mash as much as needed, boil up 10 and fill the top cooler. once mash time is up, sparge from that through the mash and into the kettle. do it all in one go. no need to split into 2 x 5gal batches.if you have a 10gal boil, that is a lot to boil off if your going for a 5 gal target batch (common size).
yakumo
